<font color="#FF0000">VERY SPECIAL FORCES</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct  3  0:14:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Silent Warrior:<br><br>
My Daddy wore a Saint Christopher's medal through five years of WW II...and was only wounded once.  I wore the same medal through two years of Viet Nam.  It didn't make me bullet proof.. but what counts is that I thought it did!  When they unloaded me from the hospital ship (C-141) it was hanging around my neck.  My Dad smiled through his tears.<br><br>
My God promises to replace that which the locust hath eaten.<br><br>
God was never my co-pilot... He was my aircraft commander!<br><br>
Tatekohomni Wambli.. your brother!
<p><code>-- Mita wasicun he omakayaki!  (Hecita Yelo) </code><p>


